question:
The MC-SIS procedure selects important variables based on the magnitudes of $\widehat{\lambda_{j1}^*$, which is the estimate of the largest eigenvalue $\lambda_{j1}^*$ from the generalized eigenvalue problem involving the matrices $\mathbf{A}_{j00}$, $\mathbf{A}_{j0X}$, and $\mathbf{A}_{jXX}$. The selected set of variables is defined as $\widehat{\mathcal{D}_{
u_n}} = \{1 \leq j \leq p : \widehat{\lambda_{j1}^*} \geq 
u_n\}$, where $
u_n$ is a pre-specified threshold. The threshold $
u_n$ is often chosen such that the size of $\widehat{\mathcal{D}_{
u_n}}$ is $n$ or $[n / \ln n]$. The term [BLANK] is used to denote the cardinality of the selected set $\widehat{\mathcal{D}_{
u_n}}$.
